        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, activation deactivates the calling app (assuming it was active), and then the new app is activated only if thereâ€™s no currently active application. This prevents the new app from stealing focus from the user, if the app is slow to activate and the user has switched to a different app in the interim. However, if you specify "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsapplicationactivationoptions/nsapplicationactivateignoringotherapps"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the application is activated regardless of the currently active app, potentially stealing focus from the user."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "You should"
                },
                {
                  "type": "strong",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " rarely pass this flag"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " because stealing key focus produces a poor user experience."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
